fields.description:
The started underlying ssh process doesn't end when running an ssh command from a Bamboo Script task. This doesn't allow the Bamboo plan to finish. Killing the process fails the build. Stopping the plan after it ran long time shows the build as successful.

A workaround is to use:
{code}
ssh -f jboss@myhost "nohup /apps/jboss/jboss-as/bin/jboss_24hf.sh start" > /dev/null 2>&1
{code}

instead of:
{code}
ssh -f jboss@myhost /apps/jboss/jboss-as/server/../bin/jboss_24hf.sh restart
{code}
